Don´t use CD-keys from the nfo-file, they are compromised! The program will record the CD-key but it doesn´t  alert you until you try and register after which you'll get a "subcription expired even if you do everything correct. The badkey will be saved even if you uninstall and re-install. To get rid of it you have to delete it in the register. DON'T USE IT! Instead dl the new keygen named TDA for the 2005 NIS and use it both to generate a CD-key and later (as dicribed in the installation guide here) for the phone activation. Enjoy! :)
